    "vs_clockwork.ponder.alt_meter.text_4": "You can also configure the sensitivity, the range at which it will start emitting a signal",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.alt_meter.text_5": "The signal strength will increase with proximity to the target altitude",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.alt_meter.text_6": "The direction setting allows you to chose which side of the target altitude the Altimeter will work",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.alt_meter.text_7": "Possible settings are: UP, DOWN and BOTH",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.alt_meter.text_8": "UP will make the Altimeter only output when approaching the target altitude from below",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.alt_meter.text_9": "DOWN will only output when approaching the target from above",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.cambered_wings.header": "Cambered wings",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.cambered_wings.text_1": "Normal wings have a base angle of attack of 0",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.cambered_wings.text_2": "This means they behave the same as they would in real life",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.cambered_wings.text_3": "Usually resulting in a nice glide",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.cambered_wings.text_4": "Cambered wings have a base angle of attack of 20",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.cambered_wings.text_5": "This means they behave as if they were tilted 20 degrees up",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.cambered_wings.text_6": "Generating a lot more lift than normal wings",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.duct.header": "Gas Ducts",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.duct.text_1": "Ducts form the core of Clockwork's gas networks.",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.duct.text_10": "Right-Clicking a leak with a Wrench will seal it back up.",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.duct.text_2": "Gas blocks can only be connected to each other with ducts.",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.duct.text_3": "Using a Wrench on a connection toggles it on or off.",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.duct.text_4": "Shift right clicking an edge with a Screwdriver cycles its type. The types are:",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.duct.text_5": "One-way",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.duct.text_6": "Filtered",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.duct.text_7": "Smart",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.duct.text_8": "Right clicking a Smart or Filtered edge with a Screwdriver lets you edit it",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.duct.text_9": "If a duct is caught in an explosion, it will become a leak and gas will violently escape!",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.flap_bearing.header": "Flap Bearing",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.flap_bearing.text_1": "Flap bearings are a unique kind of bearing",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.flap_bearing.text_2": "They still require glue,",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.flap_bearing.text_3": "but don't spin immediately when given rotation",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.flap_bearing.text_4": "Instead, they tilt when given a redstone signal",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.flap_bearing.text_5": "Analogue signal strengths allow more control over the angle",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.gyro.header": "Gyro",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.gyro.text_1": "Gyro will stabilize ship in its direction",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.gyro.text_2": "Redstone input from each side will tilt the ship",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.plane_tips.header": "Plane Tips",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.plane_tips.text_1": "Tip #1: use normal wings most of the time",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.plane_tips.text_2": "Normal wings provide enough lift for the majority planes",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.plane_tips.text_3": "Using too many cambered wings can cause excessive loop-de-looping",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.plane_tips.text_4": "Tip #2: Add a vertical stabilizer",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.plane_tips.text_5": "Having a vertical stabilizer can greatly increase your stability in the air",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.plane_tips.text_6": "Reducing 'drift' while turning",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.plane_tips.text_7": "However, do not use cambered wings",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.plane_tips.text_8": "Cambered wings will have an angle of 20",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.plane_tips.text_9": "Causing your plane to turn",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.resistor.header": "Redstone Resistor",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.resistor.text_1": "16 RPM",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.resistor.text_2": "Speed will go down depending on redstone level",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.resistor.text_3": "10.67 RPM",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.resistor.text_4": "5.33 RPM",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.resistor.text_5": "0 RPM",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.smart_flap_bearing.header": "Smart Flap Bearing",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.smart_flap_bearing.text_1": "Smart flap bearings work the same as normal ones",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.smart_flap_bearing.text_2": "Except that they have built-in redstone link slots",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.smart_flap_bearing.text_3": "Making for much more compact builds.",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.solid_delivery.header": "Solid Delivery",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.solid_delivery.text_1": "Delivery cannons and chutes can transport items in a short range",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.solid_delivery.text_2": "They have a frequency slot, similar to Redstone links",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.solid_delivery.text_3": "Cannons will only fire to chutes with the same frequency",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.solid_delivery.text_4": "Cannons will shoot out any items from the storage below",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.solid_delivery.text_5": "The benefit of Delivery cannons over something like a weighted ejector,",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.solid_delivery.text_6": "Is that the Delivery cannon can shoot between Ships.",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.solid_delivery.text_7": "Both the cannon and chute can only be placed on Depots,",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.solid_delivery.text_8": "Chutes,",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.solid_delivery.text_9": "and belts",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.wanderwand.header": "Wanderwand",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.wanderwand.text_1": "Place the wand in the Physics Infuser",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.wanderwand.text_2": "Or use the Gravitron",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.wanderwand.text_3": "This Ship is now affected by physics!",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.wings.header": "Wings",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.wings.text_1": "All blocks are affected by aerodynamics in Valkyrien Skies",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.wings.text_2": "The shape of the block can affect its aerodynamic behaviour",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.wings.text_3": "This means blocks like slabs can provide a small amount of lift",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.wings.text_4": "And experience less drag while moving through the air",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.wings.text_5": "Wing blocks amplify their aerodynamic affect",
    "vs_clockwork.ponder.wings.text_6": "They have a stronger lift force, and experience less drag",
